PWSL, PWSL General
64.1 PWSL General
� General Information
� Architecture Overview
System voltage
The system voltage strategy is to compute the battery voltage VP_PWR. Battery voltage is the highest battery
voltage acquired from available ADC on ems : VBK (VP_PWR[NC_NR_V_IGK]) and VBR (VP_PWR[NC_NR_V_RLY_
MAIN]) signals.
Accuracy of VP_PWR[NC_NR_V_RLY_MAIN] computation can depend on the con?guration NLC_V_RLY_MAIN_
PRES. Please refer to step 3 : con?guration of the reference list.
Some common threshold detections of battery voltage are also managed by the aggregate functiunality.
Corresponding battery volatge diagnosis is done by a low or high battery voltage threshold detection.
Diagnosis permits to be sure system voltage is in a correct range. System voltage is always available. If it is not
the case ems is off.

Main relay
The main relay control is done in accordance with ecu states. Main relay is release after end of every tasks of
ems, when ems actuators and sensors are no more needed, and ems locked.
Corresponding diagnosis of main relay is done on relay control signal and on relay output (VBR/KL87).

PWSL, PWSL General
Diagnosis permits to be sure that power supply for actuators and sensors behind main relay is under control :
does not stay on when it should be off, or does not stay off when it should be on.
Availability of after relay power supply (on or off) can be obtain through symptoms.
Pertinence of this diagnosis depends on the con?guration NLC_V_RLY_MAIN_PRES. Please refer to step 3 :
con?guration of the reference list.
Ignition key state
Aim of this functionality is to detect driver intentions through ignition key state. Only stable key states are
available after a debounced ?ltering of VBK signal.
Ignition key start state
Aim of this functionality is to detect driver intentions through ignition key start state. Only stable key start state
are available after a debounced ?ltering of KL50 signal (key starter position or start button).
64.1.1 General information
? The goal of the generic part of the aggregate is to deliver a single system voltage and related data ?ow,
plus the ignition key/key start state.
System voltage is the power supply voltage of ems and its related components : actuators and sensors behind
key, relays, or direct battery.
VP_PWR table are computed from the battery voltage with a ?rst level of ?ltering. Their computation are
independent of the electrical architecture, as most part of the data ?ow of this aggregate.
Ignition key state is largely used in many aggregates, but mainly as an input of ECU state. It permits to detect
several driver intentions. The ?rst one is the intention to wake-up ems or immediate engine start, the second
is to stop the engine.
A wake-up line can be availlable and supply the ECU before ignition key state.
Ignition key start state allows to start the starter motor.

Figure 64.4.1:
This ?ltering is used for noise reduction. It computes average of raw values V_RLY_MAIN_BAS on NC_VB_
SAMPLE_NR samples.
Acquisition of the raw value V_RLY_MAIN_BAS is performed every 1 ms if available.
Elsewhere an external estimation of VBR is provided.
The range of V_RLY_MAIN_MES_H_RES depends on voltage divider before the ADC converter and after VBR
(NC_V_RLY_MAIN_BRI_RATIO factor).

V_RLY_MAIN_BAS if the array was not completely ?lled by the 1ms task.

PWSL, Acquisition of after key battery voltage
Purpose of this module is to make a ?rst level of ?ltering of after key raw acquisition battery voltage (VBK is
also named KL15) and/or the after key at start raw acquisition battery voltage (KL50)

Figure 64.5.1:
This ?ltering is used for noise reduction. It computes average of raw values V_IGK_BAS/ V_IGK_ST_BAS on
NC_VB_SAMPLE_NR samples.
The acquisition of the raw values is performed every 1 ms.
The range of V_IGK_MES_H_RES depends on the voltage divider before the ADC converter and after VBK. The
ratio of the divider resistor bridge is given by NC_V_IGK_BRI_RATIO.
For KL50, it is given by NC_V_IGK_ST_BRI_RATIO.

PWSL, Acquisition of after key battery voltage
64.5.1 Initialization at reset
Before the reset event, the voltage is ramping up to the nominal value. To avoid the usage of wrong values
in the computation of the mean value, the array_sample is ?lled with the last acquisition of the raw value
V_IGK_BAS if the array was not completely ?lled by the 1ms task.
Variables ctr and LV_V_IGK_MES_CLC_RST are initialized by default with 0 at RAM init. They do not have to be
initialized at reset event in case of 1ms preemptive task update it before reset event.
This reset task is called only If NC_STATE_V_IGK_PRES = 1, 4 or 5 or NC_STATE_V_IGK_ST_PRES = 1 or 4

64.5.2 Operation at 1MS
Before the applicative RST event, a ?rst acquisition of V_IGK_MES_H_RES/ V_IGK_ST_MES_H_RES is performed.
A sample acquisition from V_IGK_BAS/ V_IGK_ST_BAS is performed at each 1ms during NC_VB_SAMPLE_NR
sample acquisition (NC_VB_SAMPLE_NR ms) before the applicative RST event but it is no guaranty, so at the
basic RST event, NC_VB_SAMPLE_NR sample acquisition from V_IGK_BAS/ V_IGK_ST_BAS is performed in one
single shot.
1ms task has to be called only if NC_STATE_V_IGK_PRES = 1 or 5 or NC_STATE_V_IGK_ST_PRES = 1 to save CPU.

� General Information
Purpose of this module is to permit to design a wake-up signal strategy named LV_WKUL.
This signal permits to wake ECU.
If no wake up acquisition is available, only ?ags LV_WKUL and LV_WKUL_CONF are computed. Other data are
not de?ned in order to save RAM/ROM.
1 ms task is performed only if project need ?ltering of V_WKUL raw acquisition or, in case of digital acquisition
of Wake up signal, if HW do not ?lter the digital input.
Action ACTION_PWSL_GetLvWkulPoll is de?ned to compute LV_WKUL even if OS stops.
� Application Conditions
Initialisation: RST
Activation: always
Deactivation: never
Recurrence: 1MS, 10MS

Figure 64.6.5:
64.6.1.2.1.1 Filtering of analogic wake up at reset
This block performs the computation of the analogical part of the wake up signal at reset.
If the array sample is not yet completely ?lled (Reset event comes before the NC_VB_SAMPLE_NR occurrence
of the 1ms task), the empty elements of this array are complete with the last raw acquisition of the wake-up
voltage, in order to compute V_WKUL_MES_H_RES (rescaled to take into account resistor bridge).
According to the value of the calibration LC_V_WKUL_FIL_RST, the result of the 1ms task is used or the analogic
raw acquisition is directly used.

According to the basic software raw value V_WKUL_BAS, after wake-up signal, the wake-up state ON / OFF
recognition is performed (LV_V_WKUL_BAS).
LV_V_WKUL_BAS is performed every 1 ms through a ?ltering of raw acquisition value of after wake-up signal
voltage (V_WKUL_BAS). Before the applicative RST event, a ?rst acquisition of LV_V_WKUL_BAS is performed
every 1 ms (1 ms task is started before the applicative RST event)
If WAKE_UP is not ?ltered, T_ADC_V_WKUL and LV_V_WKUL_BAS have not to be de?ned in order to save
RAM.

� General Information
Purpose of this module is to get ignition key position state (ON or OFF) named KL15 and the ignition key start
position state (ON or OFF) named KL50: LV_IGK_BAS and LV_IGK_ST_BAS from electrical input signals.
Filtering strategies are also included in case of analogic input. A level ?ltering is performed from the raw
acquisitions values of after key battery voltage to obtain the ignition key position state (LV_IGK_BAS) and the
key start position state (LV_IGK_ST_BAS).
The key position and the key start position state can be detected via a digital or analogic input.
Scheduling at 5ms is performed only if NLC_IGK_FAST_PRES = 1 (computation of ignition key state is required
each 5ms)

PWSL, Key position determination
64.7.1 Ignition key/key start position state acquisition present or not
If ignition key position state acquisition is not present: LV_IGK_BAS = 0 (in this case the key information can be
provided by the intersystem). If this signal is present: this acquisition calculated through the 1ms preemptive
task (LV_IGK_BAS_TMP) is copied in LV_IGK_BAS in case of analogic input or this acquisition is read directly
from infrastructure in case of digital input.
If key start position state acquisition is not present: LV_IGK_ST_BAS = 0 (in this case the key start information
can be provided by the intersystem). If this signal is present: this acquisition calculated through the 1ms
preemptive task (LV_IGK_ST_BAS_TMP) is copied in LV_IGK_ST_BAS in case of analogic input or this acquisition
is read directly from infrastructure in case of digital input.
If NC_STATE_V_IGK_PRES = 1 or 2 and no 1ms task was called before the RST event, data LV_IGK_BAS_TMP is
initialized to 0 by ECU.
If NC_STATE_V_IGK_ST_PRES = 1 or 2 and no 1ms task was called before the RST event, data LV_IGK_ST_BAS_TMP
is initialized to 0 by ECU.

64.7.1.2 Initialization in case of digital acquisition
According HW implementation, digital ignition key acquisition is ?ltered (NLC_IGK_DIG_FIL = 1) or not (0).
If the calibration LC_IGK_DIG_FIL_RST is set, the ignition key signal is ?ltered by the 1 ms task.
If this calibration is equal to 0, the direct acquisition is used to computed the ?nal ignition key status.
If the signal is HW ?ltered, the direct acquisition is used to computed the ?nal ignition key status.
In case of both analogic and digital key acquisition implemented, the ?ag LV_DIG_IGK_BAS is computed only if
LC_V_IGK_USE = 0.

Figure 64.7.9:
64.7.2 Basic Key and Key start position determination
According to the basic software raw value V_IGK_BAS, after ignition key (KL15), the ignition key ON / OFF
recognition is performed (LV_IGK_BAS_TMP).
LV_IGK_ BAS_TMP is performed every 1 ms through a ?ltering of raw acquisition value of after key battery
voltage (V_IGK_BAS). Before the applicative RST event, a ?rst acquisition of LV_IGK_BAS_TMP is performed
every 1 ms (1 ms task is started before the applicative RST event)
According to the basic software raw value V_IGK_ST_BAS, after ignition key start (KL50), the ignition key start
ON / OFF recognition is performed (LV_IGK_ST_BAS_TMP).
LV_IGK_ST_BAS_TMP is performed every 1 ms through a ?ltering of raw acquisition value of after key start
battery voltage (V_IGK_ST_BAS). Before the applicative RST event, a ?rst acquisition of LV_IGK_ST_BAS_TMP is
performed every 1 ms (1 ms task is started before the applicative RST event)
If digital acquisition is performed, and if Applicative SW do the ?ltering, the same mechanism is used.

64.7.2.2 Initialization in case of digital acquisition
According HW implementation, digital ignition key acquisition is ?ltered (NLC_IGK_DIG_FIL = 1) or not (0).
If the calibration LC_IGK_DIG_FIL_RST is set, the ignition key signal is ?ltered by the 1 ms task.
If this calibration is equal to 0, the direct acquisition is used to computed the ?nal ignition key status.
If the signal is HW ?ltered, the direct acquisition is used to computed the ?nal ignition key status.
In case of both analogic and digital key acquisition implemented, the ?ag LV_DIG_IGK_BAS is computed only if
LC_V_IGK_USE = 0.

64.7.6.1 Content of action
This action returns the same value as the last call of ACTION_PWSL_GetLvIgkPoll.
During IO start-up (before OS start), ACTION_PWSL_GetLvIgkPoll is called in order to detect the status of the
ignition key. The same key status must be used later, immediately after OS start. Using again ACTION_PWSL_
GetLvIgkPoll is not feasible, because the output could be modi?ed by its own ?ltering algorithm. Instead
ACTION_PWSL_GetLastLvIgkPoll can be used safely, because it?s only a simple getter, with no impact on its out-
put.

� General Information
This module perform the ?rst level of ?ltering of after power relay battery voltage raw acquisition.
To save ROM and CPU, this module is called only if NC_NR_V_PWR_RLY>0.
This ?ltering is used for noise reduction. It computes average of raw values V_PWR_RLY_BAS[idx] on NC_VB_
SAMPLE_NR samples.
Acquisition of the raw value V_PWR_RLY_BAS[idx] is performed every 1 ms if available.
Elsewhere an external estimation of voltage after Power Relay (idx) is provided.
The range of VP_PWR_RLY_MES_H_RES depends on voltage divider before the ADC converter and after power
relay voltage (NC_V_PWR_RLY_BRI_RATIO factor).

64.9.1.1 Power relays request computation
This part has to be called before the power relays control.
// check if vehicle moving once, inhibit is set irreversible until next reset:
If VS >0 km/h or (ACTION_FARM_GetPermission(NC_FID_CLC_PWR_RLY_REQ[NC_IDX_ENG_RLY])= 0 )
then LV_INH_ENG_RLY_OFF_ERR = 1
endif
// relay switch off due to detected SCG, but only if it ensured that vehicle is/was not runnning:
If ACTION_ERRM_GetErr(NC_IDX_ERR_PWR_RLY_EL_SCG[NC_IDX_ENG_RLY]) = 1 and
LV_INH_ENG_RLY_OFF_ERR =0 and
LV_PWL_LST_NOT_VLD = 0
then LV_ENG_RLY_OFF_ERR = 1
else LV_ENG_RLY_OFF_ERR = 0
endif
If LV_IGK = 1
then // relay switch on with ignition on:
LV_PWR_RLY_REQ[NC_IDX_ENG_RLY] = 1
T_ENG_RLY_DLY = C_T_ENG_RLY_DLY
else // relay switch off delay, decrementing counter:
If T_ENG_RLY_DLY>0 ms
then T_ENG_RLY_DLY = T_ENG_RLY_DLY - 10ms
endif
endif
// relay switch off due to ignition off or error:
If ( LV_IGK = 0 and T_ENG_RLY_DLY = 0ms ) or LV_ENG_RLY_OFF_ERR = 1
then LV_PWR_RLY_REQ[NC_IDX_ENG_RLY] = 0
T_ENG_RLY_DLY = 0 ms
endif

64.9.1.2 Main relay diagnosis con?guration
Main relay shall be switch on when ECU is switched on, that is to say : at reset event (at beginning of system
start-up).
Once all system tasks during the power-latch phase are ?nished except the main relay task and NVMY for error
management, the main relay is switched off (all actuators powered by main relay are deactivated). After the
main relay is off, the main relay OFF output diagnosis plausibility starts. When the diagnosis is ?nished, the
power latch phase is ?nished and the shutdown phase starts and after switch OFF the ECU.
//PLAUS_OFF Con?guration
If(1) ACTION_ECOP_CheckPWLLockCdn(NC_PWL_LOCK_CDN_DIAG_RLY_MAIN) & 0x80 = 0x80 //bit 7 set
Then(1)
ACTION_ERRM_RequestGetSdr(NC_IDX_ERR_RLY_MAIN_PLAUS_OFF, PRM_STATE_DIAG, PRM_ABC, PRM_
ABC_INC, PRM_ABC_DEC, PRM_ABC_MAX)
If(2) ((PRM_ABC = PRM_ABC_MAX) or (PRM_ABC = -PRM_ABC_MAX)) or
T_DIAG_RLY_MAIN_OFF >= C_T_MAX_DIAG_RLY_MAIN_OFF
Then(2)
// Main Relay "switch off" diagnosis is ?nished OR maximum delay time to lock PWL is reached.
ACTION_ECOP_ReleasePwlPhase( NC_PWL_LOCK_CDN_DIAG_RLY_MAIN)
LV_DIAG_RLY_MAIN_OFF = 0
Else(2)
//Check normal conditions to perform the main relay plaus off diagnosis
If(3) PWL_LOCK_CDN_PWSL = C_PWL_LOCK_CDN_RLY_MAIN_OFF
Then(3) PWL_LOCK_CDN_CHECK_TMP = 1
Else(3) PWL_LOCK_CDN_CHECK_TMP = 0
Endif(3)
// if minimum PWL time is elapsed and previous conditions are met
If(3) T_PWL >C_T_MIN_PWL and
PWL_LOCK_CDN_CHECK_TMP = 1
Then(3)
// Main relay is switched OFF
ACTION_PWSL_SwitchMainRelay(0)
LV_DIAG_RLY_MAIN_OFF = 1
T_DIAG_RLY_MAIN_OFF = T_DIAG_RLY_MAIN_OFF + 10ms
Endif(3)
End(2)
End(1)
//PLAUS_ON Con?guration
if (LV_VB_CDN_FCT_ST = 0)
then
LV_T_RLY_MAIN_DIAG_ON_DEC_REQ = 0
LV_T_RLY_MAIN_DIAG_ON_RST_REQ= 1

ACTION_INFR_GetLvEcuVar(OUT <PRM_LV_ECU_VAR>)
� General Information
Purpose of this module is to deliver a several single system voltage from battery voltage: battery voltage
(VBD/KL36) available through the ignition key (VBK/KL15) and main relay (VBR/KL87). The battery voltage
named VP_PWR is a table allowing to read several battery voltage, curently: battery voltage after ignition key
(VP_PWR[NC_NR_V_IGK]) and after main relay (VP_PWR[NC_NR_V_RLY_MAIN]).
NC_NR_V_IGK and NC_NR_V_RLY_MAIN represent the number of battery voltage electrical lines (index of VP_
PWR table).
These number of battery voltage electrical lines should be exclusives and comprise between 1 and NC_NR_VP_
PWR.
This module is compatible with 2 possible system con?gurations :
- con?guration 1 : with VBR acquisition,
- con?guration 2 : without VBR acquisition.
There is a limitation for the system con?guration 2, without VBR acquisition : while Key is off, battery voltage
is computed with a simpli?ed strategy. Then, for engine strategies requiring an accurate battery voltage while
key is turned off, only system con?guration 1 with VBR acquisition shall be used.

Size of array depends on project con?guration.
For maximal con?guration, elements of VP_PWR are:
? Power relays voltages
? after main relay voltage (KL 87)
? after key voltage (KL 15)
? wake up voltage
? ignition key at start voltage (KL 50)
If non of these voltage are available on the project, VP_PWR is not computed.

64.11.2 Operate 5ms : LV_IGK_FAST: Fast key position determination
Ignition key position state ON (LV_IGK_FAST remains ignition key position state OFF) is prevented in case
shutdown process has started at end of powerlatch while LV_INH_PWL_TRAN_ES_EL=1
For the scalability need LV_IGK_FAST calculation can be implemented or not.
LV_IGK_FAST can be computed internally or can come from an external request (CAN, ...)
LV_IGK_FAST uses same input than LV_IGK (?ltering done by 1ms task).
Usage of LV_IGK_FAST in 10ms task or Segment task has to be checked, the consistency of this data depends
on the priority of the 5ms task and the segment or the 10ms task.

� General Information
According to the project con?guration, the alternator load signal DUCY_ALTER_PWM is the frequential input
signal of the ECU. The raw ALTPWM signal is ?ltered with IP_ALTPWM_FIL curve, depending on ALTPWM
changes. A cold start correction factor is then applied to the ?ltered signal. If the error ?ag DUCY_ALTER_PWM
is active, the substitute value IP_GEN_LOAD_SUB, depending of N_32, is selected for ALTPWM.
It can be chosen if the output represents the hardwired load value or the value received via CAN.

64.13.2.1.1 VCC calculation
For each recurrency, ACTION_INFR_GetVccBas is called to get a VCC line value and store in the VCC array. The
ratio NC_VCC_MAX/NC_VCC_BAS_MAX is used to adapt VCC to infrastructure value (resistor divisor bridge).
For digital acquisiton, the VCC estimation is performed according to the following:
if ATIC detects a short circuit (and diagnosis is possible), the estimated voltage is set to 0V or 9.99V.
If ATIC doesn?t detect any short circuit (and diagnosis is possible), the estimated voltage is set to the nominal
voltage (C_VCC_DFT[idx])
In all other cases, the voltage is maintained to previous calculated value.

PWSL, Engine ef?ciency state
0x02 recuperation status: unfavorable
0x03 recuperation status: neutral
Status is computed from input STATE_CHA_OPT:
bit0 : bExhGasReq (exhaust gas request)
bit1 : bTankVent (tank ventilation request)
bit2 : bNoStStSecExt (no security/external stop request)
bit3 : bEnrich (enrichment request)
bit4 : bTrq (torques request)
bit5 : bHELoad (bad engine load point)
bit6 : bPTC (additional heater activation)
bit7 : bRdyToDrv (engine ready for driving - start ?nished)
The recuperation recommandation function elements may be enabled or disable through STATE_EFF_ENG_
CONF: set the corresponding bit to prevent following elements from being taken into account for recuperation
recommandation.
bit0 : Powertrain locked
bit1 : Torque at clutch threshold
bit2 : Reverse gear engaged
if bit0,1,2 set, RecuPot is disabled
bit3 : Particle ?lter regeneration ongoing (Diesel engine only)
bit4 : Catalyst heating ongoing
bit5 : Tank ventilation ongoing
bit6 : No stop mode allowed due to external or security and not inhibited by driver
bit7 : Engine full load
bit8 : Full load request for protection (gasoline engine)
bit9 : Bad engine setpoint regarding power
bit10 : Bad engine setpoint regarding regime
if bits 7,8,9,10 set, whole branch is disabled
bit11 : Secundary air pump activation request
bit12 : Engine in stop mode
bit13 : Additional heating ongoing

� General Information
Purpose of this module is to get an entry point to switch on or off the main relay and get a status of the control
command through LV_RLY_MAIN.
Upon ignition key OFF to ON transition, the ECU voltage regulator is set to ON and the core microprocessor
is reset. Then, so as to power up the system (system = ECU + actuators + sensors), the main relay has to be
switched ON (most of actuators are supplied by the main relay, before or after a fuse).

PWSL, Main relay control
Upon ignition key ON to OFF transition, the ECU enters in the post-operating phase (powerlatch included in this
phase). At its end, the system shutdown is obtained by disabling the power supply on sensors and actuators.
For that it is necessary to switch off the main relay. Then, the ECU can be switched off too.
To summarize, the main relay is switched on as soon as the ECU is switched on and it remains ON until the
ECU voltage regulator is switched off.
This module permits to perform EOL tests on Main relay. These tests can be inhibited with NLC_EOL_TEST_
MAIN_RLY = 0.
This module is scheduled at 100ms to perform the Main relay actuator tests.

64.16.3 Main relay control from tool request
The main relay control can be activated by a tool request in a repaired car or end of line phase, it allows to
diagnosis the main relay. So the diagnosis starts when a new command of main relay is done (the relay is
switched from ON to OFF or from OFF to ON).
To avoid delays in the realization of the command, the LBD function is switched off with the main relay com-
mand.
This section is activated only during Actuator tests.

� General Information
Purpose is to follow engine operating status to provide information to the recuperation potential calculation
function. Output is a bit carrier STATE_CHA_OPT:
bit0 : bExhGasReq (exhaust gas request)
bit1 : bBEMLoadLow (neutral veto con?guration request)
bit2 : bBEMLoadHigh (EGY low or high request)
bit3 : bEnrich (enrichment request)
bit4 : bTrq (torques request)
bit5 : bHELoad (bad engine load point)
bit6 : bPTC (additional heater activation)
bit7 : bRdyToDrv (engine ready for driving - start ?nished)
bit8 : bEffImpReq (Load request to improve ef?ciency)
The recuperation recommandation function elements may be enabled or disabled through STATE_EFF_ENG_
CONF: set the corresponding bit to prevent following elements from being taken into account for recuperation
recommandation.
bit0 : Powertrain locked
bit1 : Torque at clutch threshold
bit2 : Reverse gear engaged
if bit0,1,2 set, RecuPot is disabled
bit3 : Particle ?lter regeneration ongoing (Diesel engine only)
bit4 : High voltage request for fuel pump
bit5 : unused
bit6 : unused
bit7 : Engine full load
bit8 : Full load request for protection (gasoline engine)
bit9 : Bad engine setpoint regarding power
bit10 : Bad engine setpoint regarding regime
if bits 7,8,9,10 set, whole branch is disabled
bit11 : unused
bit12 : Engine in stop mode
bit13 : Additional heater activation ongoing
bit14: Lambda sensor heating

64.17.3.3.2.1 Lambda sensor heating loop
Purpose is to set the Veto and bHEload signal when a lambda sensor heating is requested.
This loop checks each component of LSHPWM_DOWN[NC_CBK_EX_NR], compared to hysteresis.
To build a global output value (1 if any of the component is over the hysteresis) a counter is incremented for
each component over hysterersis. If output value is different from 0, bHEload is set (and thereby setting the
veto signal)

64.17.3.3.2.2 Lambda sensor heating loop
Purpose is to set the Veto and bHEload signal when a lambda sensor heating is requested.
This loop checks each component of LSHPWM_UP[NC_CBK_EX_NR], compared to hysteresis.
To build a global output value (1 if any of the component is over the hysteresis) a counter is incremented for
each component over hysterersis. If output value is different from 0, bHEload is set (and thereby setting the
veto signal)

64.18.1.2.1 Alternator load reduction request
With "LV_ALTER_DI_FL" you could request a reduction or deactivation of alternator loading during engine
full load. The signal will be provided via CAN to the alternator smart device.
As main condition the ambient temperature must be in certain range to activate this feature.
If there are several "alternator disable" conditions (pedal value, vehicle speed, etc... ) ful?lled, the alternator
will be disabled for a certain time period (deactivation interval) and afterwards it will be activated for an other

PWSL, Alternator power management
time period (activation interval).
For the case that "alternator disable" conditions are valid for a longer time period you can choose between
two strategies with switch "LC_ALTER_OFF_FL_REP_SUPP":
1. Activated switch: You will have one deactivation interval and one activation interval. When the "alternator
disable" conditions are still valid the no new deactivation interval will be started. Only the "alternator disable"
conditions are once invalid a new cycle will start.
2. Deactivated switch: You will have an alternating deactivation/activation of alternator load, independent
from the duration of "alternator disable" conditions. If they are valid, a deactivation period will start.

PWSL, Alternator power management
� General Information
Alternator Power Management:
The alternator turn on instant, and also the alternator torque ramp up due to alternator turn on can be con-
trolled over CAN by the ECU. By this way a drop of engine speed can be avoided at alternator start.
The alternator turn on can be delayed after engine start depending on start temperature TCO_1_ST with the
map IP_T_MIN_ALTER_ACT. After this delay elapsed, LV_ALTER_ACT is set to 1 and alternator is ramped up with
C_LOAD_ALTER_RESP_1.
The alternator on-time T_ALTER_ACT is incremented as soon as LV_ALTER_ACT = 1. The Load response time
C_LOAD_ALTER_RESP_1 is valid until T_ALTER_ACT = 3.
For the time window 3 <T_ALTER_ACT <30, the map ID_LOAD_ALTER_RESP_2 is used. This map makes it
possible to set load response time after the alternator start.
For time T_ALTER_ACT >30, the constant value C_LOAD_ALTER_RESP_3 is used. The ?BEM? builds the mini-
mum value from C_LOAD_ALTER_RESP_3 and 3.
A load shedding during engine running is not done, STATE_ALTER_INH is initialized with 0.
When engine enters stop mode LV_STST_STOP_ACT = 1, the alternator should be turned off. Alternator restart
is done as soon as engine is leaving stop mode.
Calibration hint :
C_LOAD_ALTER_RESP_3 should be set to 0 to ensure a suf?cient stability of the bord power.
� Application Conditions

Activation: LV_ALTER_MNG_AUTH == 1 && LV_STST_STOP_ACT == 0
Deactivation: LV_ALTER_MNG_AUTH == 0 || LV_STST_STOP_ACT == 1

� General Information
The above Actions inserted in error treatment tables are valid only for ERRM 6.x.x.
For UDGI, all initialization are managed by UDGI.
The aim of this module is to diagnose each VCC line. A diagnostic controls to result no failure that VCC line
value is greater than a minimum value named VCC low diagnostic (VCC_L) and another diagnostic controls
that VCC line value is smaller than a maximum value named VCC high diagnostic (VCC_H).
A gradient diagnosis can also be performed.

� General Information
This diagnosis is based on a 2-of-3-match evaluation of a pattern (PWL_RST_x), which is saved in non volatile
memory on ?y.
At ECU power up, after the diagnosis has been executed, the PWL-pattern will be set to NC_PWL_DIAG_COD_
RST. This entry will be reset to NC_PWL_DIAG_COD_RST at the end of a PWL-phase. At the next driving cycle
this entry will be checked. If the initial pattern is not removed, the last power latch phase has not been
completed (LV_PWL_LST_NOT_VLD = 1). The reason could be a power-cut or reset.
If engine goes in running mode, then the PWL-pattern will be set to NC_PWL_DIAG_COD_ERU.
This entry will be reset to NC_PWL_DIAG_COD_RST at the end of a PWL-phase.
It will permit to know if a reset occurs during engine running.
In case of a request for a short power down (if NLC_PWL_SHO_USE = 1), indicated by LV_PWL_SHO_REQ, a
special PWL-pattern NC_PWL_DIAG_COD_SHO will be stored. Finding such a pattern at power on indicates a
short power down in last driving cycle, i.e. the last power down will be marked as valid (LV_PWL_LST_NOT_VLD
= 0) and no failure will be reported to the failure memory.
The diagnosis will always run on ECU power up. However, a failure entry will be written to the memory only if
LC_ENA_PWL_DIAG = 1. In case LV_PWL_LST_NOT_VLD = 1 an error entry is made.
The end of the diagnosis will always be indicated (LV_END_DIAG_PWL = 1), in order to set the readiness-bit of
the diagnosis, even if LC_ENA_PWL_DIAG = 0.
In case of inconsistent data, e.g. 2 of 3 mismatch or checksum error, no error entry will be made (LV_PWL_LST_
NOT_VLD = 0).
LV_PWL_LST_NOT_VLD, LV_PWL_LST_NOT_VLD_ERR_DET have to be stored in NVMY only if NLC_PWL_SHO_
USE = 1 (to save NVMY. In case of NLC_PWL_SHO_USE = 1, the history of LV_PWL_LST_NOT_VLD has to be kept,
and ?ag is not re-evaluated.
NLC_PWL_PAT_3 permits to select between 16bit triplicated pattern, or 32bit not duplicated.
In case of con?guration not supported by the project (NLC_DIAG_PWL_PRES = 0), the data
LV_PWL_LST_NOT_VLD is stubbed to 0 (means that last power latch was valid).
To save FLY channel in NVMY, the last storage in NVMY will be done with the normal storage.
For doing this, two counters will be used. When the FLY is used, the counter CTR_PWL_FLY takes a value
greater than CTR_PWL_NVMY.
At ECU start-up, if CTR_PWL_FLY has a value greater than CTR_PWL_NVMY, it means that normal PWL did not
correctly ?nished. So an error occurs.

64.24.1.3 Storage in NVMY
Two different algorithms have to be taken into account, according to the type of storage:
For storage on FLY (with action ACTION_PWSL_PwlDiag)
When the storage is done, store in CTR_PWL_FLY the value of CTR_PWL_NVMY
(CTR_PWL_FLY has to be stored in NVMY on the ?y).
CTR_SYM_PWL, PWL_RST_x and ?ags LV_PWL_LST_NOT_VLD, LV_PWL_LST_NOT_VLD_ERR_DET are stored in
NVMY on the ?y.
For "normal" storage in NVMY (at the end of PWL)
When the storage is done, store in CTR_PWL_NVMY the value of CTR_PWL_FLY + 1
(CTR_PWL_NVMY has to be stored in NVMY).
This counter is not saturated.

� General Information
The above Actions inserted in error treatment tables are valid only for ERRM 6.x.x.
For UDGI, all initialization are managed by UDGI.
For vehicles with KL50 line available, there is a possibility to detect a HW error by doing an electrical plausibility
check between state of KL15 line and KL50 line.
This plausibility diagnosis is set if the signal LV_IGK_ST is detected whereas engine conditions forbids it.

PWSL, Main relay diagnosis
� General Information
The purpose of this module is to diagnose that main relay is able to switch on or off. In case main relay can not
switch on, some actuators behind main relay are no more powered on. This diagnosis is able to detect faults
on input or on output of main relay.
Please take note that if system con?guration does not include VBR/KL87 acquisition, diagnosis of main relay
output is not possible.
The above actions inserted in error treatment tables are valid only for ERRM 6.x.x.
For UDGI, all initializations are managed by UDGI.
Figure 64.26.1:
Figure 1:
Description:
There are 2 reasons main relay can not switch :
Error on main relay control signal : main relay input is SCG/OL or SCB
Main relay has not switch on or off : main relay output is SCG/OL or SCB.

64.26.1.3 Main relay OFF output diagnosis plausibility
Error detection of main relay off output is done by comparing output relay voltage (V_RLY_MAIN_MES_H_RES)
with a threshold voltage during possible conditions.
This diagnosis is performed at the end of power latch, but before the DEAC phase (when OS is still running).
This diagnosis locks the power latch.
This strategy can detect :
main relay output at short circuit to battery voltage (SCB) : main relay stays switched on.
at ?rst NVMY initialization or if NVMY is not available, following substitute values has to be taken:
MAIN_RLY_DFT_CARRIER = 0
LV_RLY_MAIN_DFT_MEM = 0
LV_RLY_MAIN_DFT = 0
MAIN_RLY_DFT_CARRIER and LV_RLY_MAIN_DFT_MEM are stored in NVMY on ?y, only in case of main relay
error, if the ECU is powered by the main relay.

64.26.1.4 Main relay ON output diagnosis plausibility - detection relay too slow
Error detection of main relay on output is performed at reset only to detect if the main relay has been switched
on within the correct timing (detect slow relay). This diagnostic is comparable to the main relay switch on, but
is separated for having a faster reaction time. The output relay voltage (V_RLY_MAIN_MES_H_RES) is compared
with a threshold. While diagnosis is running and error free status is not yet con?rmed, safety diagnostic delays
engine start.
This strategy can detect :
main relay output at open line or short circuit to ground (SCG/OL): main relay stays switched off.
Switching-on time of main relay is too long (eg. due to low temperature)
Some projects want to inhibit the diagnosis if timer T_RLY_MAIN_DLY_DIAG is not elapsed, whereas some other
wants to go in condition, call ERRM once, and delay the diagnosis during the timer T_RLY_MAIN_DLY_DIAG. This
con?guration is selected by tuning the calibration LC_T_RLY_MAIN_DLY_DIAG_INH_USE and C_T_RLY_MAIN_
DLY_DIAG (see spec xxA04Mxx).
LV_INC_CTR_ENA is a temporary ?ag.

64.26.2 Main relay input electrical diagnosis (power stage output)
� General Information
The main relay input is driven by the ECU via an output driver. The failure detection is done by ECU Hard-
ware.
The purpose of the diagnosis is to detect electrical faults as de?ned by OBD I requirements.
Hardware can detect :
Short circuit to ground SCG, open line OL : main relay stays switched on in case of SCG, main relay stays
switched off in case of OL.
Short circuit to battery SCB : main relay stays switched off.
After activation conditions are met, the diagnosis activation is delayed for NC_PSD_DLY_RLY_MAIN_EL execu-
tions, to avoid the usage of wrong infrastructure information.

64.26.15 ACTION_PWSL_TrigMainRlyDiagFly
This action has to be de?ned only if NC_STATE_DIAG_RLY_MAIN_OFF_PRES= 2 (project without VDB)
At end of PWL, ECOP open the main relay and the ECU will be no more powered.
If it is the case, it means that main relay was not open as required, and ECU is still powered.
An error is written in NVMY in order be diagnose in the next reset.
This action is normally called only once. To avoid bad calls and destruction of NVMY, this algorithm save the
?ag only once by cycle.
If(2) LV_RLY_MAIN_DFT_TMP = 0
Then(2)
CTR_MAIN_RLY_FLY = CTR_MAIN_RLY_NVMY + 1 //do not saturate counter to make it pass through zero (if
needed)
ACTION_PWSL_FlyNvmyWriteReq()
Store in NVMY on ?y this counter
LV_RLY_MAIN_DFT_TMP = 1
End(2)
End(1)

� Function Description
64.28.1 Check permission of the diagnostic with FARM
The inhibition conditions of the electrical diagnosis are checked.
The action call ACTION_INFR_GetElDiagGenc reads the primary failure and condition information for a symp-
tom of the charge connection.
If(1) ACTION_FARM_GetPermission(NC_FID_ERR_GENC_EL) = 0 or
LV_INH_GENC_EL_DIAG_EXT_REQ = 1
Then (1)
CTR_PSD_DLY_GENC_EL = NC_PSD_DLY_PWSL_RLY_EL
tmp_cdn_diag = 0
tmp_err_diag = 0
Else(1)
If(2) CTR_PSD_DLY_GENC_EL >0
Then(2)
CTR_PSD_DLY_GENC_EL = CTR_PSD_DLY_GENC_EL -1
tmp_cdn_diag = 0
tmp_err_diag = 0
Else(2)
ACTION_INFR_GetElDiagGenc(tmp_err_diag, tmp_cdn_diag)
End(2)
End(1)

64.29.1 Generator load signal diagnosis
� General Information
The above Actions inserted in error treatment tables are valid only for ERRM 6.x.x.
For UDGI, all initialization are managed by UDGI.
Feedback of alternator, in case of HW acquisition, is diagnosed to check the range and the gradient.
Diagnosis Generator Load Signal : Gradient check is performed only if NLC_AL TER_DUCY_GRD_DIAG_PRES =
1
Diagnosis Generator Load Signal : Generator load above maximum is performed only if NLC_AL TER_DUCY_H_DIAG_PRES
= 1
Diagnosis Generator Load Signal : Generator load below minimum is performed only if NLC_AL TER_DUCY_L_DIAG_PRES
= 1

� General Information
This speci?cation perform plausibility diagnosis of LV_IGK according ECU acquisition and values received ex-
ternally.
Several key position can be received.
Values are compared to internal ECU acquisition and an error is raised if content differs.
Diagnosis is inhibited for a delay at every time ECU LV_IGK is updated.
The above Actions inserted in error treatment tables are valid only for ERRM 6.x.x.
For UDGI, all initialization are managed by UDGI.

In some project, FARM connection for NC_FID_ERR_IGK_PLAUS[NC_IDX_IGK_PLAUS_DSS_DIAG] can be the
same thanNC_IDX_FID_COM_IMOB_1_TOUT (valid debounced information for WFS_01_alt, ie valid information
of WFS_ID_Geb_autorisiert_in_Kl15" ->LV_IGK_IMOB_KEY_AUTH)

64.30.2 Plausibility KL15/ CAN signal
The Diagnosis should detect shortcut to battery of IGK(HW). The hardware-signal is compared to the signal
from CAN, if hardware show a high signal but CAN signalize 0, then a error is recognized.
There can be different states for safety issues calibrated.

PWSL, Power supply diagnosis
This diagnosis recognise if ECU was disconnected at least once during ECU was in sleep mode. If one or more
disconnections are detected during one OFF-cycle, a counter does increment once.
The diagnosis is based on feedback of the implemented engine off timer-PIC.
If STATE_T_ES_VLD_RD shows "battery off", then the counter should be incremented. If the PIC returns valid
signals, the counter should be reset.
The values from PIC are taken only once, directly after validity of signal is approved (calculated in ENSS mod-
ule). Later the PIC could be reset and deliver wrong values.
Figure 64.32.1:
PIC-States
The error entry will be done after C_CTR_VB_OFF OFF-cycles, where at least one disconnection was detected.
If one OFF- cycle is detected without disconnection, the internal counter is reset.

Name Dim Hex.Limits Phys.Limits Resol. Unit
C_V_IGK_SUB - 8000... 7FFFH -640...
639.98046875
0.0195313 V
Battery voltage substitute value when voltage acquisition after main relay is impossible while key is turned off (typical value 12,6V)
Purpose and functionality
In case of a system con?guration with NC_STATE_RLY_MAIN_PRES = 0, VBR acquisition is not available, VP_
PWR[NC_NR_V_RLY_MAIN] is equal to V_IGK_MES when Key position is on and C_V_IGK_SUB when Key position
is off.
Battery voltage estimation is the maximum value of all acquired voltage done by PWSL aggregate. In case of
non availability of all used voltage, battery voltage estimation is substitute by C_V_IGK_SUB.
At reset, VP_PWR_MMV[NC_NR_V_RLY_MAIN] = C_V_IGK_SUB in order to a better mean value during the ?rst
recurrences.
Method of calibration
C_V_IGK_SUB shall be equal to a stabilized battery voltage value. This value shall be obtained in following
conditions : ecu on and key off.
Typical Value
Typical value is 12,6v. This value depends on the nature of the battery used in the project. This value depends
also on the total quantity of current consumed by actuators or other components.

Name Dim Hex. limits Phys. Limits Resol. Unit
LC_V_IGK_USE - 0... 1H 0... 1 1 -
Purpose and functionality
PWSL performs the acquisition of the ignition key signal. This acquisition could be digital or analogic.
Method of calibration
To avoid any board effect between analogic or digital acquisition, only one source can be used for the detection
of the ignition key signal. LC_V_IGK_USE is equal to 1 if the voltage acquisition is used, or equal to 0 if the digital
acquisition is used.
This calibration switch is useless in other cases.

no typical value

Calibration switch to use VB_H_RES or V_RLY_MAIN_MES_H_RES in LV_VB_CDN_OBD_x computation (0:VB_H_RES is used/1
V_RLY_MAIN_MES_H_RES is used)
Purpose and functionality
PWSL aggregate permits to detect battery voltage thresholds.
The ?rst one is here to detect if battery voltage is greater than the calibration value C_VP_PWR_DIAG_CDN_MIN.
This is used by sensor diagnosis.
The second one is here to detect if battery voltage is inside or outside gap of voltage MIN and MAX for OBDI or
OBDII components C_VP_PWR_OBD_1_DIAG_CDN_MIN, C_VP_PWR_OBD_1_DIAG_CDN_MAX, C_VP_PWR_OBD_2_
DIAG_CDN_MIN, C_VP_PWR_OBD_1_DIAG_CDN_MAX.

functionality.

PWSL, Electrical power supply (gen)
PWSL aggregate permits to diagnose main relay is able to switch on or off. Diagnosis is performed by moni-
toring main relay contact behavior when test conditions are ful?lled.
Method of calibration
C_T_RLY_MAIN_DLY_DIAG, C_T_RLY_MAIN_PLAUS_OFF_DIAG , C_T_RLY_MAIN_PLAUS_ON_DIAG are related to
main relay component characteristic : Delay time required by relay to switch on or off.
C_V_IGK_RLY_MAIN_DIAG depends on main relay component characteristics : minimal power supply volt-
age.
C_V_RLY_MAIN_DIAG After relay threshold voltage to detect relay has switched on or off.
C_VB_RLY_MAIN_DLY_MAX_DIAG/ C_VB_RLY_MAIN_DLY_MIN_DIAG are battery voltage threshold (hysteresis)
to detect relay has switched on (used for the main relay output diagnosis plausibility ? detection relay too
slow). Hysteresis is used for voltage ramp, because switch threshold are not the same in case of positive
gradient of voltage nor negative gradient.
C_VB_RLY_MAIN_ON_MAX_DIAG/ C_VB_RLY_MAIN_ON_MIN_DIAG are battery voltage threshold (hysteresis) to
detect relay has switched on (used for the main relay ON output diagnosis plausibility). Hysteresis is used for
voltage ramp, because switch threshold are not the same in case of positive gradient of voltage nor negative
gradient.
C_VB_EXT_MIN_RLY_ON_DIAG / C_VB_EXT_MIN_RLY_DLY_DIAG are thresholds to determine if battery voltage is
OK or not, in case of PWSL acquisitions can not determine by itself the value of battery voltage.
These thresholds is compared to an external value of battery voltage, usually received by CAN from car body
unit, or battery monitoring sensor, if possible.
In case of such information is not available,
the threshold C_VB_EXT_MIN_RLY_ON_DIAG has to be calibrated to 0, thus main relay plausibility ON diagnosis
will be inhibited in case of non possible detection of battery voltage.
the threshold C_VB_EXT_MIN_RLY_DLY_DIAG has to be calibrated to 31.75V, thus main relay plausibility delay
diagnosis will not be inhibited in case of non possible detection of battery voltage. It means that error on main
relay too slow will be detected
Typical Value
Typical value for C_T_RLY_MAIN_DLY_DIAG, C_T_RLY_MAIN_PLAUS_OFF_DIAG , C_T_RLY_MAIN_PLAUS_ON_DIAG can
be around 100ms. Please note that these values shall be tuned and considered as a starting point.
Typical values are:
C_V_IGK_RLY_MAIN_DIAG = 6V
C_V_RLY_MAIN_DIAG = 6V
C_VB_RLY_MAIN_DLY_MAX_DIAG, C_VB_RLY_MAIN_ON_MAX_DIAG = 8V
C_VB_RLY_MAIN_DLY_MIN_DIAG, C_VB_RLY_MAIN_ON_MIN_DIAG = 6V
C_VB_EXT_MIN_RLY_ON_DIAG = 0V, C_VB_EXT_MIN_RLY_DLY_DIAG = 31.75V
LC_DIAG_RLY_MAIN_DLY_NO_FIL = 1
LC_RLY_MAIN_DIAG_CDN_RST = 1

If the 1ms task does not start before reset event, ignition key signal will be equal to 0 at reset, and set after the
?rst 10ms task. an event key off to key on will be performed and can be disturbing for some drivers.
To avoid this, set LC_IGK_FIL_RST = 0 and LC_IGK_ST_FIL_RST = 0
Logical value to keep ?ltering of ignition key signal during reset (1) or ?x the status to the measured voltage
(0)
Same strategy is implemented for Wake up state.
To avoid this, set LC_V_WKUL_FIL_RST to 0 (voltage acquisition) or LC_WKUL_DIG_FIL_RST [idx] for all requested
digital acquisitions.
It may be possible to maintain previous state of ignition key and ignition key start if the battery voltage is too
low. This delay is provided by these 2 timers: C_T_IGK_HLD, C_T_IGK_ST_HLD.

## Function

The Simulink diagram represents a system for acquiring and filtering the battery voltage after the main relay (VBR/KL87) in an automotive Electronic Control Unit (ECU). The system aims to provide a clean, noise-reduced measurement of the battery voltage (V_RLY_MAIN_MES) to the Engine Management System (EMS).

## Inputs

*   **VBR:** Battery voltage after relay, input to the voltage divider (R1, R2).
*   **VBR/KL87** (From Figure 64.4.1): Indicates the battery voltage availability.
*   **Actuators and Sensors** (From Figure 64.4.1): Represent other inputs and outputs associated with the EMS.
*   **NC_VB_SAMPLE_NR**: Parameter used in the averaging filter (implied from the text description).
*   **NC_V_RLY_MAIN_BRI_RATIO**:  Ratio factor used in scaling (implied).
*   **NLC_V_RLY_MAIN_PRES**:  Flag indicating the availability of VBR acquisition (implied).

## Outputs

*   **V_RLY_MAIN_MES:** Filtered battery voltage measurement sent to the EMS.
*   **V_RLY_MAIN_BAS:** Raw, unfiltered battery voltage after ADC conversion.

## Logic Flow

1.  **Voltage Division:** The battery voltage (VBR) is first scaled down by a resistor divider network consisting of resistors R1 and R2 and a capacitor C.  This is done to bring the voltage within the acceptable input range of the Analog-to-Digital Converter (ADC). This occurs within the ECU.

2.  **Analog-to-Digital Conversion (A/D):** The scaled-down analog voltage is converted to a digital signal (V_RLY_MAIN_BAS) by the ADC.

3.  **Filtering:** The digital signal V_RLY_MAIN_BAS is then passed through a filter.  The text description indicates that this is a noise reduction filter, specifically an averaging filter. It computes the average of raw values of V_RLY_MAIN_BAS based on `NC_VB_SAMPLE_NR` samples.

4.  **Output to EMS:** The filtered battery voltage, V_RLY_MAIN_MES, is then provided to the Engine Management System (EMS).

5.  **Alternate VBR source:** If VBR acquisition is unavailable (NLC_V_RLY_MAIN_PRES = 0), V_RLY_MAIN_MES_H_RES is stubbed with C_V_IGK_SUB at a reset event, indicating an alternate method for acquiring VBR.

6. **Scaling:** The range of V_RLY_MAIN_MES_H_RES depends on the voltage divider before the ADC and after VBR based on the `NC_V_RLY_MAIN_BRI_RATIO` factor.

7. **Periodic Acquisition:** The raw voltage V_RLY_MAIN_BAS is acquired every 1ms if available. Otherwise, an external estimation of VBR is provided.

The primary function of this Simulink diagram is to acquire the after-relay battery voltage and compute/stub related voltage values. It appears to be responsible for initialization and runtime measurement/calculation of relay voltage signals. The overall goal, according to the text below the diagram, is to compute or "stub" the  `V_RLY_MAIN_MES_H_RES` value based on the acquired battery voltage.

## Logic Flow

The logic flow can be broken down into the following steps:

1.  **Initialization:** The diagram starts with an initialization block `INI` which takes `fc_INI` and `[input]` and `[feedback]` signals as input. The output of this block feeds into subsequent blocks. The initialization block appears to have an internal state indicated by the `[feedback]` input.

2.  **Timing and Activation:** Function calls `fc_1MS`, `fc_5MS`, and `fc_10MS` trigger the execution of blocks `OPM_1MS`, `OPM_5MS`, and `OPM_10MS` respectively. The activation and deactivation parameters indicate that the acquisition is always activated and never deactivated.

3.  **Operational Modes (OPM):** The three "OPM" (Operational Mode) blocks (`OPM_1MS`, `OPM_5MS`, `OPM_10MS`) appear to process the input signals at different recurrence rates (1ms, 5ms, 10ms).
